  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel the <strong>butternut squash<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and cut in half</p>\n<p>Tip: Use a sharp knife drizzled with a little vegetable oil for easier chopping</p>\n<p>Scoop out the seeds and discard</p>\n<p>Slice finely into half-moons</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced butternut squash</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>baby leaf</strong> <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2083.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>vegetable stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a pot over a medium heat with 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>and once melted, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until a roux (sandy paste) has formed</p>\n<p>Stir the <strong>stock</strong> gradually into the roux and cook for 1-2 min</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>crème fraîche</strong> and stir well until combined – this is your <strong>white sauce</strong></p>",
